Reverend Father '''Raoul Desribes''' (born in 1856, died in 1940) was a French [[Jesuit]] [[Archaeology|archaeologist]] notable for his work on [[prehistory]] in [[Lebanon]], particularly the archaeological site of [[Minet Dalieh]] at [[Ras Beirut]]. He found two [[paleolithic]] bone [[harpoon]]s.<ref>Desribes, Raoul., "Harpons trouvés dans la brèche paléolithique d'Antélias", ''L'Anthropologie'', 25, 213, 1914</ref>

