'''Roane Fleming Byrnes''' (1890–1970) was a [[historic preservationist]] who spearheaded the creation of the [[Natchez Trace Parkway]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mississippiencyclopedia.org/entries/roane-fleming-byrnes/ |publisher=[[Mississippi Encyclopedia]] |title=Roane Fleming Byrnes |accessdate=August 28, 2018 }}</ref>

She lived at [[Ravennaside]], a historic mansion in [[Natchez, Mississippi]]. She was active in both historic preservation and race relations.<ref name=nrhpdoc-Ravennaside>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=79001299}}|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Ravennaside |publisher=[[National Park Service]]|author=Mary Wallace Crocker |date=February 7, 1979 |accessdate=August 28, 2018}} With {{NRHP url|id=79001299|photos=y|title=accompanying five photos from c.1902 and 1978}}</ref>

